name: pyruvate dehydrogenase (quinone)
classes: Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
With a quinone or similar compound as acceptor
reaction: pyruvate + ubiquinone + H2O = acetate + CO2 + ubiquinol
comment: Flavoprotein (FAD) [1]. This bacterial enzyme is located on the inner surface of the cytoplasmic membrane and coupled to the respiratory chain via ubiquinone [2,3]. Does not accept menaquinone. Activity is greatly enhanced by lipids [4,5,6]. Requires thiamine diphosphate [7]. The enzyme can also form acetoin [8].
